    }
</string>
    </property>
    <property name="html">
     <string>&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;
&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;
p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }
&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot; style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;docs-internal-guid-f66505e7-7fff-c887-0c4c-9ebce3bbcf50&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:16pt; font-weight:600;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:16pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000; background-color:transparent;&quot;&gt;Noli Me Tangere&amp;quot; (1887): Exposing the Colonial Reality&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;justify&quot; style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000; background-color:transparent;&quot;&gt;In 1887, Rizal published his first novel, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; color:#000000; background-color:transparent;&quot;&gt;Noli Me Tangere&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt;&quot;&gt; (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; color:#000000; background-color:transparent;&quot;&gt;Touch Me Not&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000; background-color:transparent;&quot;&gt;), a powerful social commentary that challenged the deeply ingrained corruption and oppression perpetuated by the Spanish colonial authorities. This novel was a direct critique of the Spanish friars, who held immense power over both the religious and social lives of Filipinos, and the colonial government, which systematically exploited the Filipino population. Through vivid characters such as Ibarra,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</string>
    </property>
   </widget>
   <widget class="QTextEdit" name="textEdit_3">
    <property name="enabled">
     <bool>false</bool>
    </property>
    <property name="geometry">
     <rect>
      <x>560</x>
      <y>100</y>
      <width>421</width>
      <height>301</height>
     </rect>
    </property>
    <property name="styleSheet">
     <string notr="true">
    QTextEdit {
        background: transparent;
        font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
        font-size: 10pt;
        border: none;
    }
</string>
    </property>
    <property name="html">
     <string>&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;
&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;
p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }
&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;justify&quot; style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000; background-color:transparent;&quot;&gt;Sisa, and Elias, Rizal exposed the harsh realities of Filipino life under Spanish rule. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;docs-internal-guid-5912ceaa-7fff-3ead-2b16-6569d68dffb8&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt;&quot;&gt;T&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000; background-color:transparent;&quot;&gt;he publication of &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; color:#000000; background-color:transparent;&quot;&gt;Noli Me Tangere&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000; background-color:transparent;&quot;&gt; caused an uproar among the Spanish authorities and friars. They saw the novel as a direct threat to their control and power. Spanish officials, including the Church, condemned the book, calling it blasphemous and subversive. Despite this, the novel became immensely popular among Filipinos, who saw it as a call for unity and a voice for their long-suffered plight. It sparked a renewed sense of nationalism and a desire for change, resonating with those who were yearning for &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000; background-color:transparent;&quot;&gt;justice&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000; background-color:transparent;&quot;&gt;, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000; background-color:transparent;&quot;&gt;equality&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000; background-color:transparent;&quot;&gt;, and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000; background-color:transparent;&quot;&gt;freedom&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000; background-color:transparent;&quot;&gt; from colonial oppression.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</string>
    </property>
   </widget>
   <widget class="QTextEdit" name="textEdit_4">
    <property name="enabled">
