    <property name="styleSheet">
     <string notr="true">
    QTextEdit {
        background: transparent;
        font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
        font-size: 10pt;
        border: none;
    }
</string>
    </property>
    <property name="html">
     <string>&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;
&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;
p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }
&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot; style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:16pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000; background-color:transparent;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;El Filibusterismo&amp;quot; (1891): A More Radical Call for Revolution&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;justify&quot; style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000; background-color:transparent;&quot;&gt;In 1891, Rizal published his second novel,  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; color:#000000; background-color:transparent;&quot;&gt;El Filibusterismo &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000; background-color:transparent;&quot;&gt;(The Reign of Greed), which presented an even more radical perspective on the Philippine struggle for &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000; background-color:transparent;&quot;&gt;independence&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000; background-color:transparent;&quot;&gt;. While &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; color:#000000; background-color:transparent;&quot;&gt;Noli Me Tangere d&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000; background-color:transparent;&quot;&gt;epicted the sufferings and injustices faced by Filipinos under Spanish rule, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; color:#000000; background-color:transparent;&quot;&gt;El Filibusterismo &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000; background-color:transparent;&quot;&gt;took a more &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000; background-color:transparent;&quot;&gt;revolutionary&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000; background-color:transparent;&quot;&gt; tone, highlighting the potential for armed resistance. Through the character of Simoun, a revolutionary who seeks vengeance and justice through violent means, Rizal portrayed the frustrations of Filipinos who, after enduring years of exploitation, might see violent uprising as the only solution to their problems.    &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt;&quot;&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</string>
    </property>
   </widget>
